Defendant in custody.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of three (3) years. That is eighteen (18) months initial confinement followed by eighteen (18) months extended supervision, concurrent with the sentence imposed on 15 CF 514.
The defendant has credit for 274 days.
The Court finds the defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Programs.
Conditions of extended supervision for both cases:
1) Pay court costs;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) comply with Sex Offender Registry;
4) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
5) no contact with any of the victims or anyone under the age of 18 without the agents permission, with the exception of her own children;
6) defendant is to seek and/or maintain fulltime employment at the agents discretion.
Minutes.

Defendant in custody.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Pay court costs;
3) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
4) no contact with any of the victims or anyone under the age of 18 without the agents permission, with the except of her own children;
5) defendant is to comply with the Sex Offender Registry;
7) defendant is to seek and/or  maintain fulltime employment at the agents discretion.
The defendant has 198 days credit if revoked.
